//! `[x_0, x_1, x_2, x_3, y_0, y_1, y_2, y_3]` — little-endian 64-bit limbs of
//! the x then y coordinates, **in Montgomery form** (Montgomery radix
//! `R = 2^256 mod p`), ready for [`super::p256::P256::mul_generator`] to use
//! without any conversion. No entry is the identity (`j * 16^i` is never a
//! multiple of the odd prime group order `n`), so a plain `Z = 1` lift is
//! always valid.
